"Or-Equals" and other shortcut operators

array ||= []
shorthand way for
if array has a boolean value of true (if neither false or nil) then don't do anything, but if it doesn't initialize it to a new array. 

array || array = []

"And-Equals"
&&= (rarely used)

"Plus-Equals"
+=
a += 1 means a = a + 1

- =

* = 

/=

**= (raise to a power)

&= (bitwise AND)

|= (bitwise OR)

^= (bitwise EXCLUSIVE OR)

%= modulo


You can use x += y on an instance of class (x)... This is syntactic sugar for x = x. + (y)